race.comment: A couple of key scratchings open this up for CONFIDENTIALITY (4) who debuts for the Joe Pride stable. Half-sister to top sprinter Private Eye. Trialling as though she has some of the family talent and the strong early betting push backs that assertion. REWRITE (2) is a Written Tycoon colt on debut for Michael Freedman. Plenty of trial experience dating back to May. Should be forward enough to run well. MAJESTIC LEGEND (5) is first-up since a disappointing debut in June on soft ground. Recent trials have been encouraging. Worth another chance on firmer footing this time. TRIPLE PLAY (9) appears for the first time. Half-sister to the Group 3 winner Bases Loaded from the Waller camp. Placed in both trials and McDonald rides so she is sure to attract interest. SANT GERVASI (3) and SECRET ENCOUNTER (6) are first starters that have shown enough at the trials to suggest they can make an impact.
